  "meta": {
    "title": "CAVE-Score",
    "doi": "10.1161/STROKEAHA.114.004686",
    "cff_info": "<div id=\"fieldInfoCAVE\" style=\" margin-top: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px;\">\n  <h4>CAVE Score</h4>\n  <p><i>Haapaniemi et al., 2014</i></p>\n  <p><b>DOI:</b> <a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1161/STROKEAHA.114.004686\" target=\"_blank\">10.1161/STROKEAHA.114.004686</a></p>\n  <h4>Factors and Points</h4>\n  <ul>\n    <li><b>Cortical involvement:</b>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Yes: 1 point</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li><b>Age:</b>\n      <ul>\n        <li><65 years: 1 point</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li><b>Volume:</b>\n      <ul>\n        <li>>10 mL: 1 point</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li><b>Seizures:</b>\n      <ul>\n        <li>Early seizures within 7 days of ICH: 1 point</li>\n      </ul>\n    </li>\n  </ul>\n  <h4>Risk by CAVE Score</h4>\n  <p>After a median follow-up of 2.7 years:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>0 points: <b>0.6%</b> risk</li>\n    <li>1 point: <b>3.6%</b> risk</li>\n    <li>2 points: <b>9.8%</b> risk</li>\n    <li>3 points: <b>34.8%</b> risk</li>\n    <li>4 points: <b>46.2%</b> risk</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h4>Visualization</h4>\n  <p>Refer to <b>Figure 1</b> in the publication for the Kaplan–Meier curve illustrating the timing of the first late seizure after ICH for CAVE scores from 0 to 4.</p>\n  <h4>Additional Study Information</h4>\n  <table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <thead>\n      <tr style=\"background-color: #f2f2f2;\">\n        <th style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">Category</th>\n        <th style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">Details</th>\n      </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\"><b>Score Name</b></td>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">CAVE Score</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\"><b>Population</b></td>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">\n          Derivation: 993 patients (n=764 > 7-day survivors), Helsinki (2005-2010)<br>\n          Validation: 325 patients, Lille (2004-2009)\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\"><b>Statistical Methods</b></td>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">Cox regression model</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\"><b>Validation Methods</b></td>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">\n          Internal: Retrospective cohort (University Hospital Helsinki)<br>\n          External: 325 patients, Lille (2004-2009)\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\"><b>Performance Metrics</b></td>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">\n          c-statistic: 0.81 (derivation), 0.69 (validation)<br>\n          Risk scores: 0.6% (0 points) to 46.2% (4 points)\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\"><b>Generalizability</b></td>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">Moderate to high (lower validation c-statistic)</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\"><b>Clinical Utility</b></td>\n        <td style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px;\">\n          The CAVE score is simple and easy to use, helping clinicians identify patients at higher risk for remote seizures. This can guide follow-up care and preventive strategies.\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n</div>",
    "authors": "Haapaniemi E, Strbian D, Rossi C, et al.",
    "journal": "Stroke",
    "year": 2014,
    "clinical_utility": "Background and Purpose— Seizures are a common complication of intracerebral hemorrhage (ICH). We developed a novel tool to quantify this risk in individual patients.",
    "outcome": "The CAVE Score for Predicting Late Seizures After Intracerebral Hemorrhage"
  },
  "thresholds": {
    "group1": 20.0,
    "group2": 2.0
  },
  "predictors": [
    {
      "name": "Cortical Involvement",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "No",
          "points": 0
        },
        {
          "label": "Yes",
          "points": 1
        }
      ],
      "assess": "Bleeding affecting the cortical areas of the brain, which increases the risk of remote symptomatic seizures/epilepsy."
    },
    {
      "name": "Age",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": ">65 years",
          "points": 0
        },
        {
          "label": "<65 years",
          "points": 1
        }
      ],
      "assess": "Patients younger than 65 years at the time of the hemorrhage, which increases the risk of remote symptomatic seizures/epilepsy."
    },
    {
      "name": "Volume",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "<10 mL",
          "points": 0
        },
        {
          "label": ">10 mL",
          "points": 1
        }
      ],
      "assess": "The volume of the intracerebral hemorrhage, calculated using the ABC/2 method (estimating volume from maximum dimensions in three orthogonal planes). A volume greater than 10 mL increases the risk of remote symptomatic seizures/epilepsy."
    },
    {
      "name": "Acute Symptomatic Seizures/ Early Seizures",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "No",
          "points": 0
        },
        {
          "label": "Yes",
          "points": 1
        }
      ],
      "assess": "Seizures occurring within the first seven days following the hemorrhage, which increases the risk of remote symptomatic seizures/epilepsy."
    }
  ],
